The defendant Michael A. Chmiel was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Manuf/Deliver Designer Drugs (<=3g), a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1)(hm)1.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

of Plea/Sentencing Hearing -- January 26, 2017

2:27 pm cases called. 15CF129, 16CF162, 16CF191, 16CM458. Defendant Michael A. Chmiel in court with attorney David C. Rashid & Attorney Brian Kane.  Defendant Michael A. Chmiel in custody.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Agreement stated on the record by ADA Anderson. Attorney Rashid and Attorney Kane confirm recommendation.  16CF191 & 16CF162- Defendant advised of potential punishment.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  Plea:  No Contest to Count 1 in 16CF191 & No Contest to Count 2 in 16CF162. Court accepts plea and enters JOC. Court dismisses out right Count 1 of 16CF162 & repeater enhancer in Count 1 of 16CF191. Court dismisses and reads-in Count 2 of 16CF191, Counts 3, 4, & 5 2016CF162 & 16CM458 in its entirety. Sentencing argument by ADA Anderson. Sentencing argument by Attorney Rashid. Sentencing argument by Attorney Kane. Statement by defendant. Court sentences the defendant to:
15CF129- 5 years 6 months Wisconsin State Prison to be served as 30 months Initial Confinement and 3 years Extended Supervision. Concurrent to Marquette County 15CF55. Credit for 259 days served. CONDITIONS OF ES: AODA and follow through. The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician. Court re-imposes costs not previously paid. Re-imposes Drug Buy Money.  No Contact with Justin Sertle. Terms of Agent.  DNA Sample and Surcharge ordered by the Court.  Defendant advised of right to expunge DNA record through the Department of Justice. Court finds the defendant eligible for CIP & SAP. 
16CF191- 2 years Wisconsin State Prison to be served as 1 year Initial Confinement and 1 year Extended Supervision. Consecutive to 15CF129. No credit for Time Served. CONDITIONS OF ES: AODA and follow through. The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician. Costs to be paid through authorization of DOC plus $40 Drug Buy Money.  No Contact with Justin Sertle.  Terms of Agent.  DNA Sample and Surcharge ordered by the Court.  Defendant advised of right to expunge DNA record through the Department of Justice. Court finds the defendant eligible for CIP & SAP.
